'''Brutus''' is a low-level [[free-to-play]] [[boss]] located in the [[Lumbridge cow field]], whom players defeat as part of the quest [[The Ides of Milk]], and can be fought after completion of the quest as a boss encounter. During the quest, he cannot kill the player with standard attacks (his charge and stomp attacks can still kill) and does not drop anything.

First announced at the [[Winter Summit 2026]], Brutus is designed to be accessible for low-level players. Unlike [[Scurrius]], which requires some investment before fighting him, Brutus can be reasonably fought almost immediately after starting the game and teaches players a few aspects of bossing, such as dodging telegraphed attacks.

Brutus is an excellent source for [[Clue scroll (beginner)|beginner clue scrolls]], especially for higher level players who can kill the boss quickly. He also drops [[Clue scroll (easy)|easy clue scrolls]] at a lower rate.

Upon completion of [[Desert Treasure II - The Fallen Empire]], a stronger version of Brutus, known as [[Demonic Brutus]], can be fought by feeding him an [[abyssal potato]]; one potato permits only one attempt, but these are readily available from the [[Growth (The Scar)|growth]] found in [[the Scar]].

