==Trivia==
*Brutus is the only free-to-play boss that has [[Combat Achievement]] tasks in the hard and elite tier.
*The acorn drop is a reference to [[Mod Acorn]] who developed the boss alongside [[Mod Arcane]] during [[Game Jam VII]].
*Like [[Cassius]] and the Ides of Milk quest, Brutus' name is a reference to the Assassination of Julius Caesar, specifically to Marcus Junius Brutus, one of the most prominent and well-known conspirators in the plot.
*Using an item on Brutus prompts the message {{mes|Brutus doesn't want that.}} as opposed to the usual {{mes|Nothing interesting happens.}}
*Using an empty bucket on Brutus prompts the message {{mes|You do not want to do that.}}
*Killing Brutus or his demonic variant while the player is wearing [[Cow31337Killer]]'s outfit ([[rune boots]], [[rune platebody]], [[rune plateskirt]], [[Klank's gauntlets]], [[Dharok's helm]], and [[Dharok's greataxe]]) prompts the message {{mes|You are but an imitation of a true legend.}}
*As of 27 February 2026, Brutus and his demonic variant had killed players a total of 153,350 times, of which 35 of those were hardcore ironmen. The reclaim cost from these deaths also totaled 44,200,000,000 coins.{{CiteTwitter|url=https://twitter.com/OldSchoolRS/status/2027111781286429109|date=26 February 2026|quote=Mess with the bull? You get the horns!<br />Brutus' easy & hard mode has killed players 153,550 times & 35 of those players were hardcore ironmen so far. This has cost players 44.2B 🥛|author=OldSchoolRS}}
*The [[scoreboard (Brutus)|scoreboard]] next to Brutus' pen has morse code on it that translates to [https://simpsons.fandom.com/wiki/Malk "MALK"].{{sic}}

